The paper studies competition in a general framework introduced by Immorlica et al. and proposes a new criterion for analyzing the quality of orderings in dueling games. The paper focuses on the ranking duel, which is a classic optimization problem in information retrieval (IR) and can be categorized under cs.IR. The proposed criterion is based on game theory and can be categorized under cs.GT. The paper also uses algorithms and optimization techniques, which can be categorized under cs.DS and cs.AI. Finally, the paper analyzes the quality of minimax results, which can be categorized under cs.LG.
